TECH_PARAM_1.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number of the beginning of buoyancy reduction (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_2.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions at the surface
TECH_PARAM_2.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of solenoid valve actions at the surface until the crossing of the GAP threshold

TECH_PARAM_4.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when first stabilization appears during descent to park (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached  (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of entrance in drift target range (descent)
TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to park pressure: number of entries in margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy during park phase - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions in parking
TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during park phase

TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in parking
TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions while at park depth

TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the beginning of the descent to profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the end of the descent to profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in descent
TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of entrance in drift target range
TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to profile pressure: number of entries in margin around profile pressure target  - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target profile pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of re-positioning in profile stand-by
TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: at profile pressure stand-by, number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions in drift to Profile
TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions while drifting at profile depth

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in drift to Profile
TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions during drift at profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day at the beginning of the ascent to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time of the first transmission for this cycle

TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in ascent
TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between start and end of ascent

TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth).

TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the drift at park depth.

TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit sensor data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of descent slices in shallow zone
TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Descending profile reduction Number of slices in shallow zone - NTS

TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of descent slices in deep zone
TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Descending profile reduction Number of slices in deep zone - NTF

TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of CTD measurements in drift

TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent slices in shallow zone
TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Ascending profile reduction Number of slices in shallow zone - NTS

TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of ascent slices in deep zone
TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Ascending profile reduction Number of slices in deep zone - NTF

TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Last (shallowest) pumped raw pressure sample acquired during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface (i.e. just before the cut-off pressure where the pump is stopped) (in dbars).

TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure measured just before the float dives which is then used to correct pressure on board the float for the next profile.  Note: this is a relative offset. Autocorrected.

TECH_PARAM_34.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Batteries voltage drop at Pmax, pump ON (with regard to Unom = 10.0 V) (in dV)

TECH_PARAM_35.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: real time clock status - 1= OK, 0=not OK

TECH_PARAM_37.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: grounded flag , diagnostic bit - could also be logical?  Yes/no? 0/1? Or can be number of profiles during which the float grounded

TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Grounding day relative to cycle beginning
TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number when the float grounds for the first time (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_40.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Emergency ascents - Internal count

TECH_PARAM_41.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of minutes elapsed in the day of the float first emergency ascent.

TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Pressure that triggered the first emergency ascent

TECH_PARAM_43.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions in emergency ascent
TECH_PARAM_43.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Emergency ascent - pump actions at emergency depth

TECH_PARAM_44.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: 1st Emergency ascent relative day (to 1st cycle day)
TECH_PARAM_44.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Day number of the float first emergency ascent (relative to mission start day).

TECH_PARAM_45.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control successfully considered.

TECH_PARAM_46.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control rejected by the float (due to out of range value or remote control syntax error).
